for some element formula_55 of the general linear group of invertible formula_56 matrices with entries in formula_5. This defines an equivalence relation between formula_46 matrices formula_47 of rank formula_2, for which the equivalence classes are denoted formula_61.

We now define a coordinate atlas. For any formula_62 homogeneous coordinate matrix formula_47, we can apply elementary column operations (which amounts to multiplying formula_47 by a sequence of elements formula_55) to obtain its reduced column echelon form. If the first formula_2 rows of formula_47 are linearly independent, the result will have the form
