== The Grassmannian as a homogeneous space ==
The quickest way of giving the Grassmannian a geometric structure is to express it as a homogeneous space. First, recall that the general linear group formula_196 acts transitively on the formula_2-dimensional subspaces of formula_4. Therefore, if we choose a subspace formula_199 of dimension formula_2, any element formula_201
can be expressed as
:formula_202
for some group element formula_203,
where formula_204 is determined only up to right multiplication
by elements formula_205 of the stabilizer of formula_206:
:formula_207
under the formula_196-action.

We may therefore identify formula_152 with the quotient space
:formula_210
of left cosets of formula_211.

If the underlying field is formula_212 or formula_213 and formula_196 is considered as a Lie group, this construction makes the Grassmannian a smooth manifold under the quotient structure. More generally, over a ground field formula_5, the group formula_196 is an algebraic group, and this construction shows that the Grassmannian is a non-singular algebraic variety. It follows from the existence of the Plücker embedding that the Grassmannian is complete as an algebraic variety. In particular, formula_211 is a parabolic subgroup of formula_196.

Over formula_212 or formula_213 it also becomes possible to use smaller groups in this construction. To do this over formula_212, fix a Euclidean inner product formula_222 on formula_4. The real orthogonal group formula_224 acts transitively on the set of formula_2-dimensional subspaces formula_152 and the stabiliser of a formula_2-space formula_228 is 
:formula_229,
where formula_230 is the orthogonal complement of formula_206 in formula_4. 
This gives an identification as the homogeneous space
:formula_233.
If we take formula_144 and formula_235 (the first formula_2 components) we get the isomorphism
