:formula_243

In particular, this shows that the Grassmannian is compact, and of (real or complex) dimension .

== The Grassmannian as a scheme ==
In the realm of algebraic geometry, the Grassmannian can be constructed as a scheme by expressing it as a representable functor.

===Representable functor===
Let formula_244 be a quasi-coherent sheaf on a scheme formula_245. Fix a positive integer formula_2. Then to each formula_245-scheme formula_248, the Grassmannian functor associates the set of quotient modules of
:: formula_249
locally free of rank formula_2 on formula_248. We denote this set by formula_252.

This functor is representable by a separated formula_245-scheme formula_254. The latter is projective if formula_255 is finitely generated. When formula_245 is the spectrum of a field formula_5, then the sheaf formula_258 is given by a vector space formula_4 and we recover the usual Grassmannian variety of the dual space of formula_4, namely: formula_152.
By construction, the Grassmannian scheme is compatible with base changes: for any formula_245-scheme formula_263, we have a canonical isomorphism
::formula_264

In particular, for any point formula_265 of formula_245, the canonical morphism formula_267
induces an isomorphism from the fiber formula_268 to the usual Grassmannian formula_269 over the residue field formula_270.

