== The Plücker embedding ==

The Plücker embedding is a natural embedding of the Grassmannian formula_152 into the projectivization of the formula_2th Exterior power formula_298 of formula_4.
::formula_300

Suppose that formula_41 is a formula_2-dimensional subspace of the formula_3-dimensional vector space formula_4. To define formula_305, choose a basis formula_306 for formula_72, and let formula_305 be the projectivization of the wedge product of these basis elements:
formula_309
where formula_310 denotes the projective equivalence class.

A different basis for formula_72 will give a different wedge product, but the two will differ only by a non-zero scalar multiple (the determinant of the change of basis matrix). Since the right-hand side takes values in the projectivized space, formula_312 is well-defined. To see that it is an embedding, notice that it is possible to recover formula_72 from formula_305 as the span of the set of all vectors formula_315 such that 
::formula_316.

=== Plücker coordinates and Plücker relations ===
The Plücker embedding of the Grassmannian satisfies a set of simple quadratic relations called the Plücker relations. These show that the Grassmannian formula_1 embeds as a nonsingular projective algebraic subvariety of the projectivization formula_318 of the formula_2th exterior power of formula_4 and give another method for constructing the Grassmannian. To state the Plücker relations, fix a basis formula_321 for formula_4, and let formula_41 be a formula_2-dimensional subspace of formula_4 with basis formula_176. Let formula_327 be the components of formula_328 with respect to the chosen basis of formula_4, and formula_330 the formula_2-component column vectors forming the transpose of the corresponding homogeneous coordinate matrix: 
:: formula_332

For any ordered sequence formula_333 of formula_2 positive integers, let formula_335 be the determinant of the formula_77 matrix with columns formula_337. The elements formula_338 are called the Plücker coordinates of the element formula_53 of the Grassmannian (with respect to the basis formula_321 of formula_4). These are the linear coordinates of the image formula_305 of formula_72 under the Plücker map, relative to the basis of the exterior power formula_344 space generated by the basis formula_321 of formula_4. Since a change of basis for formula_72 gives rise to multiplication of the Plücker coordinates by a nonzero constant (the determinant of the change of basis matrix), these are only defined up to projective equivalence, and hence determine a point in formula_348.

For any two ordered sequences formula_349 and formula_350 of formula_291 and formula_352 positive integers, respectively, the following homogeneous quadratic equations, known as the Plücker relations, or the Plücker-Grassmann relations, are valid and determine the image formula_353 of formula_1 under the Plücker map embedding:
:: formula_355

where formula_356 denotes the sequence formula_357 with the term formula_120 omitted. These are consistent, determining a nonsingular projective algebraic variety, but they are not algebraically independent. They are equivalent to the statement that formula_305 is the projectivization of a completely decomposable element of formula_298.

When formula_361, and formula_362 (the simplest Grassmannian that is not a projective space), the above reduces to a single equation. Denoting the homogeneous coordinates of the image formula_363 under the Plücker map as formula_364, this single Plücker relation is
::formula_365

In general, many more equations are needed to define the image formula_353 of the Grassmannian in formula_348 under the Plücker embedding.

== Duality ==
Every formula_2-dimensional subspace formula_369 determines an formula_370-dimensional quotient space formula_371 of formula_4. This gives the natural short exact sequence:
::formula_373

Taking the dual to each of these three spaces and the dual linear transformations yields an inclusion of formula_374 in formula_375 with quotient formula_376
::formula_377

Using the natural isomorphism of a finite-dimensional vector space with its double dual shows that taking the dual again recovers the original short exact sequence. Consequently there is a one-to-one correspondence between formula_2-dimensional subspaces of formula_4 and formula_380-dimensional subspaces of formula_375. In terms of the Grassmannian, this gives a canonical isomorphism
::formula_382

that associates to each subspace formula_369 its annihilator formula_384.
Choosing an isomorphism of formula_4 with formula_375 therefore determines a (non-canonical) isomorphism between formula_387 and formula_388. An isomorphism of formula_4 with formula_375 is equivalent to the choice of an inner product, so with respect to the chosen inner product, this isomorphism of Grassmannians sends any formula_2-dimensional subspace into its formula_380}-dimensional orthogonal complement.

==Schubert cells==
The detailed study of Grassmannians makes use of a decomposition into affine subpaces called &quot;Schubert cells&quot;, which were first applied in enumerative geometry. The Schubert cells for formula_1 are defined in terms of a specified complete flag of subspaces formula_394 of dimension formula_395. For any integer partition 
: formula_396
of weight
::formula_397

consisting of weakly decreasing non-negative integers
:formula_398 
whose Young diagram fits within the rectangular one formula_399, the Schubert cell formula_400 consists of those elements formula_401 whose intersections with the subspaces formula_402 have the following dimensions
::formula_403

These are affine spaces, and their closures (within the Zariski topology) are known as Schubert varieties.

As an example of the technique, consider the problem of determining the Euler characteristic formula_404 of the Grassmannian formula_28 of -dimensional subspaces of . Fix a formula_406-dimensional subspace formula_407 and consider the partition of formula_28 into those -dimensional subspaces of that contain and those that do not. The former is formula_409 and the latter is a rank formula_2 vector bundle over formula_411. This gives recursive formulae:
::formula_412

Solving these recursion relations gives the formula: formula_413 if formula_3 is even and formula_2 is odd and
::formula_416
otherwise.

===Cohomology ring of the complex Grassmannian===
Every point in the complex Grassmann manifold formula_417 defines a formula_2-plane in formula_3-space. Mapping each point in a k-plane to the point representing that plane in the Grassmannian, one obtains the vector bundle formula_420 which generalizes the tautological bundle of a projective space. Similarly the formula_380-dimensional orthogonal complements of these planes yield an orthogonal vector bundle formula_422. The integral cohomology of the Grassmannians is generated, as a ring, by the Chern classes of formula_420. In particular, all of the integral cohomology is at even degree as in the case of a projective space.

These generators are subject to a set of relations, which defines the ring. The defining relations are easy to express for a larger set of generators, which consists of the Chern classes of formula_420 and formula_422. Then the relations merely state that the direct sum of the bundles formula_420 and formula_422 is trivial. Functoriality of the total Chern classes allows one to write this relation as
::formula_428

The quantum cohomology ring was calculated by Edward Witten. The generators are identical to those of the classical cohomology ring, but the top relation is changed to
::formula_429
reflecting the existence in the corresponding quantum field theory of an instanton with formula_430 fermionic zero-modes which violates the degree of the cohomology corresponding to a state by formula_430 units.

==Associated measure==
