<doc id="373872" wikidata="Q8037004" url="?curid=373872" title="Worshipful Company of Broderers">
<text>The Worshipful Company of Broderers is one of the livery companies of the City of London. Broderers were workers in embroidery; the organization of Broderers existed in at least 1376, and was officially incorporated by a royal charter in 1561. As the craft of embroidery has lost its importance as a trade, the company has become less of a trade association for broderers. Instead, the company is now, as are most livery companies, a charitable foundation.

The company is the forty-eighth in the order of precedence for livery companies. Its motto is &quot;Omnia Desuper&quot;, Latin for &quot;All From Above&quot;.

The livery hall of the Broderers, Broderers&#x27; Hall, stood on Gutter Lane from 1515 until its destruction in the London blitz. The Broderers now dine in Mercers&#x27; Hall.

== Arms ==
